title: Bug 110566 - Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression is set
description: When setting a filter expression like `row[0] equals to 0`, the data set is returning the wrong result or just returning a null result set.
OB: The data set is returning the wrong result or a null result set when an invalid filter expression like `row[0] equals to 0` is set.
EB: The data set should not return any result or return a proper error message when an invalid filter expression like `row[0] equals to 0` is set.
SR: Fix the data set logic to handle invalid filter expressions properly and either return no result or display a clear error message.
